<task id="AIPU2-086" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build PlaybookGalleryWidget for Context Pane</title>
    <phase>4D</phase>
    <tags>frontend, widgets, playbooks</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-073</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    When the SpaarkeAi shell is in the Welcome stage, the Context pane should show a gallery of
    available playbooks so users can browse and select one before starting a chat. This was not
    possible in R1 (the context pane only showed source documents after a chat turn). The
    PlaybookGalleryWidget implements ContextWidget and renders available playbooks as Fluent v9
    cards with descriptions and capability badges. When a user selects a playbook, the widget
    dispatches a playbook_selected event to the PaneEventBus 'conversation' channel so
    ConversationPane and AiSessionProvider can initialize the session with that playbook.
  </prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with React 19, Fluent v9, and event-driven architecture experience.</role>
  <goal>
    Users can browse and select playbooks from the Context pane before starting a chat.
    Playbook selection dispatches a typed event to PaneEventBus. Widget registered in
    ContextWidgetRegistry.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read ADR-021 to confirm Fluent v9 Card component usage and design token constraints.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/context/PlaybookGalleryWidget.tsx implementing ContextWidget.</step>
    <step>Define PlaybookGalleryData type: { playbooks: PlaybookSummary[] } where PlaybookSummary has id, name, description, capabilityBadges (string[]), iconName.</step>
    <step>Render each playbook as a Fluent v9 Card with: playbook name as card title, description body text, capability badges rendered as Fluent v9 Badge components.</step>
    <step>On card selection (click): call useDispatchPaneEvent() to dispatch to the 'conversation' channel a playbook_selected event carrying the selected playbook id and name.</step>
    <step>Visually highlight the currently selected card (Fluent v9 selected state or border token).</step>
    <step>Handle empty playbook list: render a Fluent v9 EmptyState illustration with instructional text.</step>
    <step>Register PlaybookGalleryWidget in ContextWidgetRegistry.</step>
    <step>Write unit tests: (a) playbooks render as cards with correct content; (b) clicking a card dispatches playbook_selected to 'conversation' channel; (c) empty list renders EmptyState.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Available playbooks render as Fluent v9 Cards with name, description, and capability badges.</criterion>
    <criterion>Clicking a playbook card dispatches playbook_selected event to the 'conversation' PaneEventBus channel.</criterion>
    <criterion>Selected card is visually highlighted using Fluent v9 tokens (no hard-coded colors).</criterion>
    <criterion>Empty playbook list renders an EmptyState, not a blank pane.</criterion>
    <criterion>Widget registered in ContextWidgetRegistry and renders in ContextPaneController during playbook-gallery stage.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests for card rendering, selection dispatch, and empty state pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
